    "body": "> Did you run a node with the flag `--rpc.gascap 0`?\r\n\r\nMost definitely not\r\n\r\n```\r\n    --rpc.gascap value             (default: 50000000)\r\n          Sets a cap on gas that can be used in eth_call/estimateGas (0=infinite)\r\n\r\n```\r\nIn other words: allow caller to use infinite gas. If I do that, of course it can be DoS:ed. An attacker can allocate all my ram,or spin the cpu forever.  ",
